VThiruvaiyaru Jayashri presented\u000aa pleasant vocal\u000arecital under the `Eppadi\u000aPaadinaro' series, organised\u000ajointly by Rasika\u000aRanjana Sabha and Sri\u000aKrishna Sweets at the FGN\u000aHall of the Sabha in Tiruchi\u000arecently.All India Radio artists\u000aSatchidhdanadam on the\u000aviolin and Tiruchi Rengarajan\u000aon the mridangam gave\u000aable support. From start to\u000afinish Jayashri's rendition\u000awas upbeat sagging nowhere\u000ain her two hour programme.\u000aSelecting kritis\u000afrom popular ragas, save\u000athe Lalitha Panjamam (`Sri\u000aParama Purusham'), she\u000awas quite at home in all of\u000athem.Vibrant and exhaustiveJayashri's `Ba Saravana\u000aBhava' in the raga Bilahari,\u000a`Rajagopalam' in Mohanam\u000aand `Parama Bhava' in Purvikalyani,\u000aspoke volumes of\u000aher skill in the craft with\u000aher vibrant sargams, apt\u000aswaras and exhaustive niravals.She was quite at ease in\u000aall her numbers which included\u000a`Dhanam Tharum'\u000aand `Karpagame Kanparai'\u000a(Madhyamavathi) and the\u000atillana in Khamas.Violin by Madurai Satchidhanandam\u000awas very\u000amuch in tune with the \u000avocalist\u000aand the vibrant thani\u000aby Tiruchi Rengarajan\u000amade the concert one\u000amemorable.
